nvektiven das Ziel, das proliferierende Stilgebaren des Kulteranismus auf die klassischen Maximen der Rhetorik herunter zu brechen. Er wähle dabei einen schändlichen Sprachgebrauch, um einen noch schändlicheren in die Schranken zu weisen, alles um der Perspicuitas willen.  aFrancisco de Quevedo’s satirical poetry is commonly viewed as grotesquely comical, a manifestation of what Bakhtin called the “Carnivalesque.” But not all of his satirical poetry fits this interpretation. In this study the author investigates the aggressivity and obscenity of Quevedo’s work, and particularly his personal invectives against Luis de Góngora, a poet of the previous generation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aInvektive. 4aSiglo de Oro. 4aStilfragen. 4aVersdichtung. 4aWortspiele. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aInvectives.  aPoetry.  aSiglo de Oro.  aStyle.  aWord Play.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103777740 cprintz978311027464640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311029595540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110295955423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110295955/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2014